{
  "_comment": "DAX golden-result fixtures for the A1-A4 DAX depth track (loom-next-level ws-lineage-depth A5). Each fixture asserts the NUMERIC result of a DAX query over the seeded Sales/Date/Customer star schema in reference-data/*.csv. A5 seeds ONLY the functions the loom-native engine supports TODAY (the 3-regex translator: EVALUATE <Table>, EVALUATE TOPN(N,<Table>), EVALUATE ROW(\"L\", CALCULATE(SUM|COUNT|AVERAGE|MIN|MAX(T[c])))). A1/A2/A3 ADD their functions' golden rows to THIS file in the SAME PR that implements the fold (status:'implemented'). The vitest provenance gate (dax-golden-fixtures.test.ts) recomputes every 'expect.value' from the CSV reference data in pure JS so a wrong golden fails locally; the live Playwright 'dax-golden' project asserts the same numbers against real Synapse serverless. See README.md for the fixture format + how to add a row.",
  "provenance": {
    "source": "reference-data/{Sales,Date,Customer}.csv — deterministic, hand-verifiable",
    "referenceEngine": "Power BI Desktop parity is reproduced by fixtures.ts::referenceEvaluate (pure JS over the same CSV rows); the CSV IS the reference model, so goldens never drift from a live tenant.",
    "salesTotalsCrosscheck": "SUM(Amount)=3500 (2023=1650, 2024=1850); 12 rows; MIN=100; MAX=600; AVG=3500/12"
  },
  "fixtures": [
